com.gotenna.sdk.data

Class GTCommandCenter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTCommandCenter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GTConnectionManager.GTConnectionListener, GTConnectionManager.GTDeviceTypeChangedListener

    public final class GTCommandCenter
extends java.lang.Object
implements GTConnectionManager.GTConnectionListener, GTConnectionManager.GTDeviceTypeChangedListener
    A singleton where all commands to the goTenna are sent from. Use this singleton to send various commands and messages to the goTenna.

    Created on 2/11/15.

      • setGoTennaGID

        public void setGoTennaGID(long gid,
                          java.lang.String username,
                          GTErrorListener errorListener)
        Sends the SET GID command to the goTenna.

        This GID will act as the goTenna's ID. Anyone wishing to communicate with this goTenna will need to send a message to this specific GID.

        Updates the UserDataStore with the user's new GID and username. Will create a new User if one does not exist already.

        Parameters:
        gid - The GID to assign to the goTenna.
        username - The name of the user who's GID this is.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.

      • sendBroadcastMessageMaxHopsMesh

        public void sendBroadcastMessageMaxHopsMesh(byte[] outgoingData,
                                            com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTSendCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                                            GTErrorListener errorListener)
        Sends a broadcast message out to every goTenna. A broadcast is also referred to as a SHOUT. This is because every nearby goTenna will received this message. Broadcast messages cannot be encrypted, their data is sent as plaintext.

        This function is only available to Super SDK users. Sends broadcast with the maximum number of hops on goTenna Mesh. Shouts are automatically sent with max hops on Pro, so you do not need to use this function for the goTenna Pro, only goTenna Mesh.

        Parameters:
        outgoingData - The message's data, such as text, preferably formatted in some easily parse-able format.
        responseListener - The response listener callback for the command.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.

      • resendBroadcastMessage

        public void resendBroadcastMessage(byte[] outgoingData,
                                   com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTSendCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                                   GTErrorListener errorListener,
                                   int resendId)
        Re-sends a broadcast message out to every goTenna. A broadcast is also referred to as a SHOUT. This is because every nearby goTenna will received this message. Broadcast messages cannot be encrypted, their data is sent as plaintext. If you don't know what a resend id is do not use this function.

        resendId - The id of the message to resend that was returned in the previous GTResponse or GTError.

      • resendMessage

        public void resendMessage(byte[] outgoingData,
                          long receiverGID,
                          com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTSendCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                          GTErrorListener errorListener,
                          boolean willEncrypt,
                          boolean shouldNotResendWithMoreHops,
                          int resendId,

        Resends a message out to a goTenna with the specified GID. Private and group messages may be encrypted if desired. If you don't know what a resend id is do not use this function.
        Parameters:
        outgoingData - The message's data, such as text, preferably formatted in some easily parse-able format.

        willEncrypt - Indicates whether the outgoingData will be encrypted or not using the SDK built in encryption system.
        shouldNotResendWithMoreHops - Indicate that for this message, we should not try to resend the message with more hops if it fails the first time.
        resendId - The id of the message to resend that was returned in the previous GTResponse or GTError.
        isPliMessage - Indicated if this message is a periodic location info message. Set to false if you don't know what this means.

      • createMulticastGroup

        public boolean createMulticastGroup(long multicastGroupGID)
        Allows the user to create their own multicast group. A multicast group works just like a regular group except there is no encryption, and you do not need to know who is in the group to join.

        Only pre-approved SDK users can leverage this functionality.

        Parameters:
        multicastGroupGID - The GID of the multicast group.
        Returns:
        True if the function ran successfully, false otherwise. Failure due to not having SDK Supertoken.

        Set the geo region on the goTenna Mesh so that it know which frequencies it should operate on. You must determine which region your user is currently in using GPS and tell the goTenna which region you are operating in as per FCC rules.
        Parameters:
        place - The place or region the goTenna is currently operating in.
        responseListener - The response listener callback for the command.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.

      • sendGetGeoRegion

        public void sendGetGeoRegion(GTCommandCenter.GTGeoRegionListener geoRegionListener,
                             GTErrorListener errorListener)
        Retrieves the Geo Region that the goTenna Mesh believes it is operating in. The goTenna mesh remembers which region you last told it and save that region in flash memory. It will continue to operate in that region unless you tell it to switch regions using sendSetGeoRegion(Place, GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener, GTErrorListener)
        Parameters:
        geoRegionListener - The response listener callback that is invoked when the region is retrieved.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.

      • sendStoreDateTimeEmergencyMessageV1

        public void sendStoreDateTimeEmergencyMessageV1(java.lang.String emergencyMessage,
                                                com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                                                GTErrorListener errorListener)
        Sends a command to the goTenna V1 to let it know what the current time is.

        Also sends a pre-formatted emergency message to be stored that contains the user's name and gps coordinates.

        This emergency message will be sent from the goTenna if the user taps the reset button on the goTenna 3 times.

        To update the user's gps coordinates for the emergency message, use UserDataStore.getCurrentUser() along with User.updateLocation(double, double, float, long)

        This command is automatically sent once every minute via GTStoreDateTimeEmergencyManager.

        Parameters:
        responseListener - The response listener callback for the command.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.
        emergencyMessage - The emergency message to be displayed.

      • sendSetFrequencyChannels

        public void sendSetFrequencyChannels(java.util.List<GTFrequencyChannel> frequencyChannelsList,
                                     com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                                     GTErrorListener errorListener)
                              throws GTInvalidFrequencyChannelException
        Sets the frequency channels that will be used by the goTenna as control and data channels.

        Only sets frequencies for the V1 goTenna. For goTenna Mesh use sendSetGeoRegion(Place, GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener, GTErrorListener). For goTenna Pro use sendSetProFrequencyChannels(List, DataRateMask, GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener, GTErrorListener).

        Will throw UnsupportedOperationException if used with limited SDK.

        Parameters:
        frequencyChannelsList - The channels that will be used by the goTenna. One of these must be marked as a control channel.
        responseListener - The response listener callback for the command.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.
        Throws:
        GTInvalidFrequencyChannelException - When an invalid frequency was used.

      • startEmergencyBeaconBroadcast

        public void startEmergencyBeaconBroadcast(com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener responseListener,
                                          GTErrorListener errorListener)
        Start the goTenna's Emergency beacon. This forces the goTenna to broadcast it's stored emergency message that is set via GTStoreDateTimeEmergencyManager.setEmergencyMessage(String).

        The Emergency message will continue to broadcast until the battery on the goTenna dies, the goTenna is power cycled, or stopEmergencyBeaconBroadcast(GTCommand.GTCommandResponseListener, GTErrorListener) is called.

        Parameters:
        responseListener - The response listener callback for the command.
        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.

      • stopEmergencyBeaconBroadcast

                                         GTErrorListener errorListener)

        Parameters:

        errorListener - The error listener callback for the command.
